  "description": [
    "j 1 Hebe in Broadway Fair Hebe banished Heaven for one sad fall No more thy smiles proud Junos heart appal No nectar now from thy amphora dnps No more false Jove drinks nectar from thy lips The jewelled vessel of celestial mould From which the bevrage of Olympus rolld A jug of common earth replaces now The best the Croton taxers will allow But ah the liquid from that pitcher poured Outshines the nest Olympus could afford And thou fair Hebe thou art honored more Dispensing Croton in a Broadway store Than in the service of that artful pleader Who cheated thee EuropaDanoLeda And scandalized his own high court celestial By taking twenty shapes profane or bestial Poor Hebe now no more the God shall jilt her Queen of the Croton Goddess of the B liter Pouring in ceaseless and transparent tide A chrystal rill completely purified Long may her graceful hand the filtered stream Send sparkling forth like a dissolving beam Long may the crowd with admiration rife Cling to the Croton as the fount of life While all the family of Uncle Sam Drink the pure current of the Diaphragm W M G Hebe has to pay"
